Practioners of digital humanities often employ text analysis to look for patterns across a single text, or across a corpus of text that may be too large for a single human to read. Python includes several libraries that address text analysis, including nltk and sci-kit. Before we get to those, we'll discuss some fundamental concepts of text analysis, especially as they relate to pre-processing of the text (to make it amenable to analysis) and the methods and limitations of some common methods for analysis. 
